I know nothing about him, and care nothing about him. It's all his own fault;
he is rightly served, sir. Why does a man leave a lovely woman ? What else can
he expect ? I don't pity him in the least,—he ought to have been here.

I do, really. You must remember, my love, the sort of man I am;
you ought to be proud of me. If I was such a person as—as, for instance, your
friend's husband; if I were like him, indeed—
